<br>
Loot is allocated by the discretion and consensus of the Fire and Fury Leadership Council.  Accordingly, should you have a disagreement with a loot allocation decision, take your concern to the officer distributing the loot, or another officer if the distributing officer is not available.  Complaining in any other channel, other than directly with an officer, is not acceptable.  <br>
<br>
Loot is allocated based on the following quantitative and qualitative factors:<br>
<br>
1: Attendance (Quantitative):  Quite simply, show up for work or you don't get paid.  Each individual member keeps track of his own attendance in it's own designated forum.  It is the individuals responsibility to keep this as up to date as possible as this factor serves as the general benchmark for allocating loot.<br>
<br>
2: Class and Guild Need (Qualitative):  The nature of EQ mandates that certain classes be given preference for certain types of loot to manage a raid force properly.  To that end, this factor will be used judiciously to allocate loot in a manner that maximizes the overall effectiveness of the guild's raid force, while at the same time seeking to avoid the pitfalls of a &quot;critical locus&quot; scenario.<br>
<br>
3: Merit (Qualitative):  Guild members who distinguish themselves by accomplishing tasks that go above and beyond the regular course of membership will be afforded additional consideration, ceterus paribus.  Examples of activities warranting a &quot;badge of merit&quot; include researching and assisting in the completion of quests, providing valuable strategic and tactical information to the leadership, and assisting other members in obtaining keys and character flags.  The goal of this factor is to recognize bona fide excellence of service to the guild.  <br>
<br>
4: Seniority (Quantitative and Qualitative):  Seniority is measurable in terms of when a particular person became a full member of the guild and in the nature of their service to the guild.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">OTHER LOOT CONSIDERATIONS:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
1: Applicants and Probationary Members:  Loot will be allocated to applicants at the discretion of the Leadership.  Prior to any loot being allocated to applicants, the membership will be canvassed to ensure that the item in question does not represent an upgrade to an existing member.  Probationary Members will be allocated loot that does not represent a significant upgrade to existing members.  &quot;Choice&quot; loot will generally not be allocated to Probationary Members.<br>
<br>
2: Passing on Loot:  Should you wish to forego on a particular item please inform the distributing officer as soon as possible.<br>
<br>
3: Trickle-down Loot:  Where an item is allocated that upgrades an existing item that was allocated by the guild, the replaced item is to be handed back to the distributing officer for reallocation.  If the replaced item was not allocated by the guild, the reallocation of said item is at the discretion of the owner.<br>
<br>
4: Unofficial Raids:  Loot acquired during unofficial raids is allocated at the discretion of the Raid Leader.  It is the duty of the Raid Leader and officers, or senior members if officers are not present, to distribute loot from these encounters in accordance with these guidelines.<br>
<br>
5: Raid Looting:  Applicants and Probationary Members are not permitted to loot corpses unless expressly instructed to do so by an officer or Raid Leader.  Any loot from guild raids is to be handed over to guild officers at the earliest possible time.<br>
<br>
6: Attendance:  Do not expect to be allocated &quot;choice&quot; loot from a raid that you did not attend.  Exceptions to this rule are at the sole discretion of the Leadership.<br>
